Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped), then finely chop (see ingredients for amount).

Trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed and cut into roughly 1cm pieces), then cut into roughly 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the cold @water for the rice{200%ml}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{100%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave the rice to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, pop the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @chermoula spice mix{1/2}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British chicken thighs{3} into a #medium bowl{} with the remaining @chermoula spice mix{1/2} and a third of the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix to coat.

Lay the chicken thighs flat on a lightly oiled baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Discard any marinade left in the bowl.

Once the aubergine has roasted for about ~{5%minutes}, add the chicken tray to the middle shelf to roast until browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through half the parsley.

When everything is ready, share the harissa rice between your plates and top with the roasted aubergine. Slice the chicken into 1cm thick pieces and lay on top.

Sprinkle over the chilli (use less if you don't like too much heat) and remaining parsley. Drizzle with the remaining yoghurt to finish. Enjoy!